description:
&lt;p&gt;Care Assistant (Day &amp; Nights)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Penylan House Nursing Home, Cardiff&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Full time 38.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Up to £9.63 per hour&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Have you helped an elderly neighbour before? Do you show empathy for other people? Have you helped raise children? And how did it make you feel?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If your answer is anything along the lines of &#39;it made me feel pretty good!&#39; - you are the person that we are looking for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Linc Cymru are offering the opportunity to join our team as a Care Assistant, based in our Penylan House Nursing Home, in Cardiff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We don&#39;t look at application forms just for qualifications or work history - we look for the person underneath all of that.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We provide the training - we can teach you how to do the role. The only thing we can&#39;t teach is how to be a naturally caring person.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;So if you check on your elderly neighbour, do the weekly shop for your family, help raise children, offer to help on school trips, you have what we can&#39;t teach and we want you to join our team. With a dedicated Learning &amp; Development Team, we will provide all the training you need, such as All Wales Induction Framework to ensure that you succeed and excel in this role!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The role (and our residents!) will keep you on your toes - no two days will be the same. From personal care to joining in with activities, this is a varied role that will send you home with a great sense of achievement and pride.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The shifts are on a rolling rota, so you&#39;ll always know what days you are working each week - great for planning ahead! You will work 3 shift one week, 4 shifts the next week with every other weekend off.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We offer a higher rate of pay if you hold a NVQ/QCF Level 2 in Health and Social Care for Adults. Rates of pay vary from £8.94 - £9.63 per hour.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The advert will close at 23:45 on 19th November 2020. We reserve the right to close this vacancy when we are in receipt of sufficient applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So, don&#39;t delay - apply today.&lt;/p&gt;
